Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.76,0:00:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.66,0:00:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she came.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.53,0:00:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though she's ruined, her attitude\Nis still the same as it was before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.97,0:00:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's gotten even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.10,0:00:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she say where\Nshe was staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.64,0:00:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. She said she had no cash on\Nhand and told me to get it from her hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.55,0:00:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She probably still\Nthinks she's rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.61,0:00:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Which hotel was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.78,0:00:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,She said it was\Nthe Steigent Hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she's really\Ngoing to pay her bill.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying at such\Na third-rate hotel...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.43,0:00:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.83,0:00:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You. .. Come to think of it.. .\Nyou were engaged to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.93,0:00:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Come to think of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.41,0:00:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. H-Hello?! Police?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.11,0:01:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,J-Just now.. .\NThat serial killer...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.44,0:01:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.14,0:01:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.31,0:01:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know\Nwhere my coat is?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.41,0:01:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.42,0:01:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I hung my coat\Nby the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.28,0:01:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.48,0:03:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.68,0:03:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.12,0:03:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman by the name of Eva\NHeinemann should be staying there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.89,0:03:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes. I shall connect you\Nto her room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.96,0:03:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Please wait one moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.49,0:03:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.24,0:03:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.00,0:03:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I was thinking of killing\Nyour former fianc√©e...Eva Heinemann.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.91,0:03:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.11,0:03:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Thank you for waiting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We called her,\Nbut she's not picking up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.22,0:03:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Get me her room number.\NOh, no, umm...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.72,0:04:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'd like to send her a fax,\Ncould you tell me her room number?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.99,0:04:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.23,0:04:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}She's in room 402.\NOur fax number is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.58,0:04:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,402...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.59,0:04:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good. Mr. Baul isn't in his office\Nand isn't answering his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.09,0:04:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your partner won't come\Nno matter how long you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm guessing that he became Tenma's\Nlawyer to win Tenma's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.54,0:04:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But Tenma made a complete\Nconfession and, in the end, escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.21,0:04:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He couldn't defend that,\Nso he's resigned as Tenma's counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you going to quit too,\NMr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.96,0:05:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't plan on doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's a fact that\NTenma escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.70,0:05:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Before he escaped, as his lawyer,\NI wanted him to trust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.10,0:05:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Then do you believe in Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.81,0:05:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe what\Nhappened in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.28,0:05:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe everything\Nthat Tenma has said?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.28,0:05:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't believe any of it,\Ndo you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard the news\Nthat Tenma escaped,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.79,0:05:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I had the same reaction\Nas I did back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.50,0:05:54.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When he disappeared from us\Nand tried to shoot Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's happening again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Tenma escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the way that you believed\Nin your father and became a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.72,0:06:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The telephone's just been ringing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.06,0:06:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The media is in an uproar\Nabout whether Verdemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the great lawyer,\Nwill continue to defend Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.97,0:06:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them I have no comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.37,0:06:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But that won't\Ncalm the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.57,0:06:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them that I'll hold a press\Nconference after I've reexamined the facts!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.91,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, don't let\Nanyone into my office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.92,0:06:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, but you have a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.65,0:06:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.99,0:06:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You let him in?!\NI won't see anyone today!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.79,0:06:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay. I told him that\Nand tried to turn him away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.33,0:06:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But he insisted that\Nhe was going to wait here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.33,0:06:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.93,0:07:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, he's with the German\NFederal Criminal Police Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.90,0:07:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The BKA?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.51,0:07:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over the Rainbow...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.78,0:07:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a nice song.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.92,0:07:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe it was the theme song of\Nthe radio station that your father ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.69,0:07:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.03,0:07:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.30,0:07:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,406...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.33,0:07:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,405...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.94,0:07:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,404.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.71,0:07:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Room 402...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.12,0:07:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.26,0:07:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Guten tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.63,0:08:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. G-Guten tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.91,0:08:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.42,0:08:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the guest who\Nwas staying here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.88,0:08:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.29,0:08:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. I came to visit the guest\Nwho was staying in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.26,0:08:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Didn't this guest\Ncheck out already?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.09,0:08:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.50,0:08:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,See? There's no one\Nhere anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.41,0:08:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.45,0:08:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.21,0:08:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the reports on Tenma\NI've seen during my investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.18,0:08:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I've taken the closest\Nlook at your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.46,0:09:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an elaborate report.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.96,0:09:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard rumors about you,\NMr. Verdemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.63,0:09:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a hero in\Nthe legal world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.40,0:09:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You've probably come here upon\Nhearing about Tenma's escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.70,0:09:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately,\NI have no information to give you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.48,0:09:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Escape, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.78,0:09:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Actually, I'm on a long\Nvacation at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.62,0:09:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way, my long vacation may\Nhave been an escape as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.52,0:09:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm. .. Excuse me,\Nbut I have no time for chit-chat.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.23,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it is a long work habit, but\NI can't freely travel without direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I end up making themes\Nfor my travels.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.64,0:09:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for this journey\Nis this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.31,0:10:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I don't have time.\NPlease leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.89,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,No, let me talk a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.72,0:10:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have anything\Nto say about Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not here to\Ntalk about Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.90,0:10:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.30,0:10:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I only heard about\NTenma's escape on the way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.27,0:10:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.84,0:10:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, this book...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.14,0:10:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I've become intensely interested in finding\Nout about the writer of this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.31,0:10:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But this writer has\Nhad many pseudonyms.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.48,0:10:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Of them,\Nonly Klaus Poppe was German.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.82,0:10:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I was curious\Nand as I investigated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.29,0:10:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I came across someone\Nwho was Poppe's acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.59,0:10:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.00,0:10:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.37,0:10:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father's radio station had a\Nprogram called "The World's Fables."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.64,0:11:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,According to records,\NPoppe's work, "Where am I?"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.11,0:11:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Was aired in the August of '66.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.68,0:11:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen records\Nof your father's trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.19,0:11:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the espionage case that\Nshook post-war West Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.26,0:11:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.83,0:11:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father entered\NCzechoslovakia several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.33,0:11:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He was just meeting with\Na picture book artist,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.40,0:11:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so it wasn't examined\Nor noticed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.07,0:11:29.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm suggesting that your father\Nmight have been old friends
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with this picture book artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.45,0:11:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had many acquaintances\Ninvolved with his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.72,0:11:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He used to meet with countless\Npeople to arrange programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.79,0:11:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're saying that\Nthey weren't that close?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.06,0:11:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But according to my investigation,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.93,0:11:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Klaus Poppe usually met people\Nat his chief editor's house
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.16,0:11:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,or at his vacation home,\Nan old farm in the Czech suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.84,0:12:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But your father met with him\Nat a certain mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.97,0:12:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.61,0:12:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Poppe never used the mansion\Nunder the name Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.39,0:12:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,When he used the mansion,\Nhe called himself Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.73,0:12:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He was someone with a very important\Npost in the Czechoslovakian Secret Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.21,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.88,0:12:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Spy kid! Spy kid!\NSpy kid! Spy kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.59,0:12:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.15,0:12:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.03,0:13:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! If you don't like that,\Nprove that he's innocent!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If the father's dirty,\Nthe son's dirty, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.44,0:13:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Spy kid! Spy kid! Spy kid !\NSpy kid! Spy kid! Spy kid! Spy kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.51,0:13:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just want to learn\Nabout Franz Bonaparta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.88,0:13:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I know of no such person!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.12,0:13:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In Czechoslovakia in '66,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.75,0:13:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}your father met Klaus Poppe\Nat a certain mansion, didn't he?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.59,0:13:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A picture book artist and\Nthe owner of a radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.60,0:13:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.63,0:13:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When he went by\Nthe name Klaus Poppe,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he never used\Nthe Red Rose Mansion.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.31,0:13:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}When he met your father\Nat the Red Rose Mansion,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.88,0:13:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}he wasn't meeting him as Klaus\NPoppe, but as Franz Bonaparta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:14:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As someone who was important to\Nthe Czechoslovakian Secret Police.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.26,0:14:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a false charge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.39,0:14:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't care whether or not\Nyour father was a spy.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.23,0:14:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,My father wasn't a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.27,0:14:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your father should have known\Nwho Franz Bonaparta really was.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.34,0:14:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not involved!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.54,0:14:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your father knew what went on in\Nthe Red Rose Mansion, didn't he?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.61,0:14:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.78,0:14:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.02,0:14:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is innocent! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.18,0:14:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.95,0:14:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Contact me when\Nyou feel like talking.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.66,0:14:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'll keep on saying it: I don't care if\Nyour father was a spy or not.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.06,0:14:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I just want to learn\Nabout Franz Bonaparta.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.71,0:14:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:14:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.48,0:15:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann,\Nyou have a call from your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.39,0:15:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.16,0:15:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Umm... Your wife is\Ncalling from the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.20,0:15:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.51,0:15:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.94,0:15:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You're finally getting out, huh?\NThat's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.82,0:15:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.38,0:15:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come and\Npick you up right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.54,0:15:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.94,0:16:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,C-Calm down.\NListen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.64,0:16:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive the car, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.99,0:16:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll understand if we talk.\NAnyway, calm down, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.46,0:16:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me what you have to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.73,0:16:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.76,0:16:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is Eva Heinemann?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.93,0:16:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.80,0:16:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.27,0:16:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't act dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.57,0:16:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you guys\Nare trying to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.44,0:16:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,"You guys"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.91,0:16:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop the car.\NLook ahead and keep going!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.48,0:16:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that you're\Nboth after Eva's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,"Eva's life"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.12,0:16:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"You guys"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.19,0:16:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're partners\Nwith that man, Baul!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.39,0:16:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Baul?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.66,0:16:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the man I shot at the library\Nat the University of Munich!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.60,0:17:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't allow any more casualties.\NAnswer me! Where is Eva?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.61,0:17:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It all began when\NI saved Johan's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.84,0:17:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He's taken many lives\Nsince then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.81,0:17:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Many, many lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.52,0:17:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.12,0:17:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let there\Nbe any more victims.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.16,0:17:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.42,0:17:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.83,0:17:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Move the car!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.53,0:17:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true,\Nwhat you just said?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.60,0:17:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it true?!\NCan I trust you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.61,0:17:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,My father...\Nwas suspected of espionage.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.62,0:17:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards,\NI proved his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.49,0:17:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But he really was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.43,0:18:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I believed in my father's innocence\Nand studied hard to become a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.93,0:18:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I found something\Nwhen I was a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.84,0:18:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Decisive proof that\Nmy father was a spy...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.07,0:18:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.91,0:18:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since then,\NI could never believe in anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"The great, crusading lawyer?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.88,0:18:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,"The hero of the legal world?!"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh. A man\Nwho doesn't believe in anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.96,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I really was the son of a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.54,0:18:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I found\Nthat notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.64,0:18:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since I found that notebook\Nthat my father had written in the 60's.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.58,0:18:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As I flipped through\Nthe pages of that notebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.82,0:18:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,everything I had believed\Nabout my father crumbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.49,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no mistake.\NMy father was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.73,0:19:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The notebook had records of contact\Nwith the Czechoslovakian Secret Police,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.30,0:19:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,written in\Nan indecipherable code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The mysterious people that my father\Ncontacted included Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.81,0:19:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Was something about the Red\NRose Mansion written in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.91,0:19:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.72,0:19:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.38,0:19:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That man, Baul, probably got close\Nto you so he could get that notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.86,0:19:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is that notebook\Nright now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.49,0:19:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,At my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.31,0:19:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.11,0:19:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.\NHe was after your father's notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.42,0:20:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letter addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.42,0:20:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He predicted that\Nyou would come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.03,0:20:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Help me, Kenzo.\NHelp me, Kenzo."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,"Come quickly to\Nthe Red Rose Mansion."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean\Nthat Eva's safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.90,0:20:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't her handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.54,0:20:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's toying.. .\NHe's toying with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.72,0:20:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.19,0:20:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in the pile of old records.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Over the Rainbow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.16,0:20:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.33,0:20:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.60,0:20:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But if someone gets it,\Nyour father will...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.54,0:20:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.86,0:21:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I trust you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.70,0:21:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What you told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.13,0:21:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're doing...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.00,0:21:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't be of any help.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.24,0:21:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But can I trust you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't trust anyone, who\Ncarries one of these around, too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.87,0:22:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I want to believe.{\i0}
